      • AclFirewallRule

        public AclFirewallRule(NetContext nctx,
                       com.microsoft.z3.Context ctx,
                       boolean action,
                       com.microsoft.z3.DatatypeExpr source,
                       com.microsoft.z3.DatatypeExpr destination,
                       java.lang.String string_src_port,
                       java.lang.String string_dst_port,
                       int protocol,
                       boolean directional)
        Creates a firewall rule with a set of parameters
        Parameters:
        nctx - the z3 net context
        ctx - the z3 context
        action - the action of the rule in boolean format (ALLOW=true, DENY=false)
        source - the DataType expression of the source address of the rule
        destination - the DataType expression of the destination address of the rule
        string_src_port - the string representing the port source interval of the rule
        string_dst_port - the string representing the destination port interval of the rule
        protocol - the level 4 protocol encoded as integer value (it is based on the enumeration class of the jaxb object)
        directional - if the rule needs to be considered also in reverse

      • AclFirewallRule

        public AclFirewallRule(NetContext nctx,
                       com.microsoft.z3.Context ctx,
                       boolean action,
                       java.lang.String source,
                       java.lang.String destination,
                       java.lang.String string_src_port,
                       java.lang.String string_dst_port,
                       int protocol,
                       boolean directional)
        Creates a firewall rule with a set of parameters
        Parameters:
        nctx - the z3 net context
        ctx - the z3 context
        action - the action of the rule in boolean format (ALLOW=true, DENY=false)
        source - the source address of the rule in a string format
        destination - the destination address of the rule in a string format
        string_src_port - the string representing the port source interval of the rule
        string_dst_port - the string representing the destination port interval of the rule
        protocol - the level 4 protocol encoded as integer value (it is based on the enumeration class of the jaxb object)
        directional - if the rule needs to be considered also in reverse
